 Storage Solutions
 -----------------
 - The candidate should consider expert in Linux development including user land and kernel space. 
 - Special emphasis on storage stack including Linux IO stack, VFS, iSCSI implementations such as
 - - LIO, iSCSI Enterprise and LVM.
 - Clearly able to articulate DFS concepts and has demonstrable proficiency in one of the file systems; 
 - - HDFS, FUSE, ZFS, JFS, log file systems, GlusterFS, Lustre.
 - Linux device driver experience and the skill necessary to enhance any existing driver is a necessary.
 - Distributed programming and experience with Apache zookeeper and dlm is a plus.
 - Basic understanding of SR-IOV, RNIC, RDMA, IB and how they can be leveraged in building solutions


